1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,752
<i>Why are you still here?</i>

2
00:00:02,836 --> 00:00:04,504
<i>We can't get out.</i>

3
00:00:04,587 --> 00:00:06,589
<i>There's nothing we can do.</i>

4
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:07,799
<i>We're trapped.</i>

5
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:10,010
<i>All the entrances and exits have bombs.</i>

6
00:00:10,093 --> 00:00:12,345
- [CABRAL] <i>What are you doing here?</i>
- [AREZA]<i> I know I can help you, sir.</i>

7
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:13,388
<i>Areza,</i>

8
00:00:13,471 --> 00:00:15,390
<i>you'll have a hard time</i>
<i>in your current state.</i>

9
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:16,391
<i>I can do it, sir.</i>

10
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,518
<i>I'm also trained for bomb disposal.</i>

11
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,562
<i>And I know I can help them.</i>

12
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:22,480
<i>Surprised, Mr. Roja?</i>

13
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>You thought I'd rot in jail.</i>

14
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:29,654
<i>I've waited a long time</i>
<i>for this day, you bastard!</i>

15
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:31,698
- [MAGNUS GRUNTS]
- [LUCAS] <i>Get him, Homer!</i>

16
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:33,825
<i>Have mercy!</i>

17
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:35,577
<i>- Please, have mercy.</i>
- [MAGNUS GRUNTS]

18
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:38,163
<i>- Wendy?</i>
- [MAGNUS GROANS]

19
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:39,539
<i>Why are you also here?</i>

20
00:00:39,622 --> 00:00:43,710
[LUCAS] <i>Is she the woman</i>
<i>you said you used to live with?</i>

21
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:47,046
[EMIL]<i> When Jacinto and I were</i>
<i>planning this,</i>

22
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:52,510
<i>we agreed to just scare the hostages.</i>

23
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:56,014
<i>He said we shouldn't hurt anybody.</i>
<i>Except for one person.</i>

24
00:00:56,097 --> 00:00:58,850
<i>And then he showed me your picture.</i>

25
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:02,437
<i>No one should get hurt aside from me?</i>

26
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,647
<i>Sounds like Jacinto's very mad at you.</i>

27
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:05,774
<i>I don't know him!</i>

28
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:10,403
<i>Looks like someone has</i>
<i>a lot of anger toward your ex.</i>

29
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,113
<i>Someone connected to Jacinto.</i>

30
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:16,409
<i>Do you think my mother knows</i>
<i>it only contains sand?</i>

31
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:17,911
<i>She probably does, right?</i>

32
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:20,371
<i>We don't know the answer to that yet.</i>

33
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,874
<i>That's why we need to focus first.</i>

34
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:24,793
<i>Let's think of how we'll get this through.</i>

35
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:27,712
[GRUNTING]

36
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:35,637
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:44,938
[COUGHING]

38
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:46,773
Well?

39
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:52,112
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:01,121
She still needs IV antibiotics
and monitoring.

41
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:03,873
Her infection markers aren't stable yet.

42
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:07,752
I thought you said she was doing okay
and responding to the medicine.

43
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:09,838
Yes, she's responding.

44
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,381
But as I said,

45
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:13,007
she hasn't fully recovered yet.

46
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:15,218
If we don't treat this properly,

47
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:19,347
it can progress into sepsis
or internal bleeding.

48
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:21,558
[COUGHING]

49
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:23,226
What's happening?

50
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:26,020
Doc! Why is she coughing?

51
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:27,021
[GASPING FOR AIR]

52
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:29,858
- It's like she can't breathe!
- I need to get a nebulizer.

53
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:32,026
Have her sit up so she can breathe.

54
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,653
Turn this crank.

55
00:02:33,736 --> 00:02:35,738
- Oh, hang in there, Leni.
- Just a moment.

56
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,868
[GWEN] Leni, wait for a bit.

57
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:45,623
[LENI GASPING FOR AIR]

58
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:52,672
[FOREBODING MUSIC SWELLS]

59
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:03,766
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRUNTING]

60
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:16,362
[COUGHS]

61
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,701
Why don't you help me?

62
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:23,745
Hurry up.

63
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:30,501
[GRUNTING]

64
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:38,509
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:44,265
Move it.

66
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,316
Go.

67
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:58,863
Don't think for a second

68
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:01,449
that I've forgotten about
what you did to my brother.

69
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,494
Don't blame us.

70
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,455
Your brother died because of you.

71
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:09,249
[SCOFFS]

72
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,794
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GROANS]

73
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:14,504
Because of me?

74
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,089
- I dare you to say that again!
- [GROANS]

75
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:19,801
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

76
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:20,843
No!

77
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:21,844
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

78
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:24,389
Olsen!

79
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:25,932
Put those down!

80
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:29,894
Put those down!

81
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:35,358
Put those down if you don't want me
to blow your brains out!

82
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,985
I said put those down!

83
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:42,740
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

84
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:45,535
[ROMAN] Go over there!

85
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:59,465
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,791
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SCREAMING]

87
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,836
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING]

88
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,254
[SCREAMS]

89
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:40,381
[BLOWS LANDING]

90
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:41,674
[GRUNTING]

91
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:43,843
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [BODY THUDS]

92
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:45,470
Fin!

93
00:05:45,553 --> 00:05:47,346
[GRUNTING]

94
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:50,725
[BLOW LANDS]

95
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:54,353
[GRUNTING]

96
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,901
- [GRUNTS]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

97
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:01,110
[GUNSHOTS]

98
00:06:03,237 --> 00:06:07,742
- [SCREAMING]
- [GUNSHOTS]

99
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:12,330
[GUNSHOTS]

100
00:06:12,413 --> 00:06:15,458
- [GRUNTING]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,959
[GUN THUDS]

102
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,086
Dado!

103
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:19,087
[BODY THUDS]

104
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:21,714
Go after them!

105
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,216
- Copy that!
- [GRUNTS]

106
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:29,097
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:39,941
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:48,116
[SCREAMING]

109
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:53,037
[GRIM MUSIC BUILDS]

110
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:54,956
- [WOMAN SCREAMS] Liam!
- [OLSEN] Enough!

111
00:06:55,039 --> 00:06:57,083
[OLSEN, DADO GRUNTING]

112
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,502
[DISTANT WOMAN SCREAMS]

113
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:02,380
[BOTH GRUNTING]

114
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,883
[DADO GRUNTS IN PAIN]

115
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,927
[OLSEN GROWLS]

116
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,512
[GROANS]

117
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:11,848
[BODY THUDS]

118
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:13,933
Ice…

119
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:16,102
[MAN] My gun!

120
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:19,439
- I'm okay.
- [HUFFS]

121
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,773
- [KICK LANDS]
- [OLSEN] Ah!

122
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:22,150
[ICE GASPS]

123
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,110
- [ICE] No! Don't hurt him!
- [STOMPS]

124
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:26,362
[VOICE TREMBLING]
Don't hurt him anymore! Please!

125
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,989
[SOBS] No!

126
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:29,824
Please! Don't do it!

127
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:32,034
Please! No!

128
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:34,579
Please! I'm begging you!

129
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:38,082
Leave him alone. Don't shoot him.

130
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,542
[SOBS]

131
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,419
- Olsen!
- [MAN] All right then.

132
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:42,920
[LIAM] Luna?!

133
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:52,722
[GUN COCKS]

134
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:59,770
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:07,904
So you're still alive.

136
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:10,031
- You're dead.
- [SCOFFS]

137
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:15,244
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GWEN] Why you--

138
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:16,704
[LIAM GRUNTING]

139
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:22,668
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTING]

140
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:27,006
[PANTS]

141
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:32,637
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,481
[BOTH GRUNTING]

143
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:44,815
[THWACKS]

144
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:47,902
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

145
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,907
[GRUNTS]

146
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:55,952
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

147
00:08:58,412 --> 00:08:59,622
[GRUNTS]

148
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,168
[GWEN GRUNTING]

149
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,380
[GROANS IN PAIN]

150
00:09:07,463 --> 00:09:10,383
[GRUNTS]

151
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,888
[LIAM, GWEN GRUNTING]

152
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,682
[THWACKING]

153
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:24,188
- [GRUNTS, BREATHES HEAVILY]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,777
- [GRUNTS HEAVILY]
- [BODY THUDS]

155
00:09:31,362 --> 00:09:37,285
[GRUNTING LOUDLY]

156
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:39,704
[HEAVING]

157
00:09:41,872 --> 00:09:43,874
[GRUNTS HEAVILY]

158
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:47,670
- [GWEN WHIMPERS, GASPS FOR AIR]
- [HISSING]

159
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:49,547
[GRUNTS HEAVILY]

160
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:51,841
[GROANS]

161
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:55,970
[LIAM PANTING]

162
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:04,145
[COUGHS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

163
00:10:04,228 --> 00:10:05,771
[GWEN GRUNTS]

164
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:07,898
[BODIES THUD]

165
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:18,367
[BOMB TICKING SOUND EFFECT]

166
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,999
- [SLAMS]
- [BODY THUDS]

167
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:31,172
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:47,938
- [DOOR OPENS]
- [BREATH QUIVERS]

169
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:50,483
- Hide. Now.
- What do we do?

170
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:52,943
- Hide. Go. Now.
- Yes, chef.

171
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,570
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

172
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:57,490
[MUTTERING] This is bad.
This is really bad.

173
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:04,580
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PANTING]

174
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:15,883
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PANICKED BREATHING]

175
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,302
There's nowhere to hide here.

176
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:21,931
Chef, what do we do?

177
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,812
The ceiling. That's right.

178
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:29,855
Hurry!

179
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:31,899
Joy, we're out of time. Move faster.

180
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:33,275
Joy!

181
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,819
[GRUNTS]

182
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:37,822
[PANICKED BREATHING]

183
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:38,989
[LUNA] Hurry.

184
00:11:41,992 --> 00:11:45,287
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

185
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:46,539
[JOY GRUNTS SOFTLY]

186
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:48,791
- Faster!
- [JOY GROANS]

187
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,377
- Mm!
- [LOCKERS CREAKING]

188
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:08,602
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:11,939
[JOY'S BREATH HITCHING]

190
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:21,449
[HAUNTING MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:23,659
[PANICKED BREATHING]

192
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:29,623
[HAUNTING MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:32,877
[GASPS LOUDLY]

194
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,587
Shh!

195
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:43,220
[HAUNTING MUSIC CONTINUES]

196
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:57,860
[INHALES SHARPLY, BREATH QUIVERS]

197
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:03,324
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:09,205
[BOMB TICKING SOUND EFFECT]

199
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:21,842
[DOOR SLAMS SHUT]

200
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,719
[EXHALES OF RELIEF]

201
00:13:23,802 --> 00:13:24,762
[WAILS]

202
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:26,889
I thought we were going to die!

203
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,766
Keep your voice down!

204
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:31,018
Joy, get it together!
Get it together, okay?!

205
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:34,605
But what are we going to do?!
What if they come back?!

206
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:37,525
- What if-- [MUFFLED SCREAMING]
- Stop it.

207
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:39,693
You'll get us all killed.

208
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:41,070
Calm down, Joy.

209
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:45,741
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:47,493
Homer.

211
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:49,912
Go talk to your ex.

212
00:14:04,176 --> 00:14:05,344
Wendy.

213
00:14:10,558 --> 00:14:13,435
I've been thinking about
who instructed Jacinto

214
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:16,355
not to hurt anyone except you.

215
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:18,691
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:21,902
Who was Jacinto's accomplice
who's mad at you?

217
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:26,490
I don't know if that's true.

218
00:14:27,491 --> 00:14:31,954
Maybe your boss just wanted me
to get paranoid and mess with me.

219
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:35,165
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:38,502
I have never played with your feelings.

221
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:41,630
I was serious about you, Wendy.

222
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:47,720
[CAP CLICKS]

223
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,391
[CAP CLICKS]

224
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,102
[WATER BOTTLE THUDS]

225
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:58,314
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

226
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:00,858
Shouldn't you be nice to me?

227
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:03,527
That's enough, Homer.

228
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,947
It might be easy for you
to forget everything,

229
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,700
but it isn't for me.

230
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:15,247
You never visited me when I was in jail.

231
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:18,417
It's impossible that you didn't know
because that was before you went to jail.

232
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:23,631
I didn't want to have any connection
with you anymore.

233
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,007
Because…

234
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:30,262
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:34,099
Did you ever love me, Wendy?

236
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:39,438
I tried.

237
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,653
I was hurt by what you did.

238
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:48,989
You abandoned me, Wendy.

239
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,535
I loved you.

240
00:15:54,828 --> 00:15:58,832
I dreamed of having children with you.
But what did you do?

241
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:01,794
I'm glad we didn't have a child.

242
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:07,466
I'd have felt bad for the kid,
having a father like you.

243
00:16:09,426 --> 00:16:12,221
I got into that trade
because I wanted to save

244
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:14,974
a huge amount of money
for our future family.

245
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:17,851
But I was unlucky.

246
00:16:17,935 --> 00:16:19,520
I was unlucky in business.

247
00:16:20,729 --> 00:16:22,356
And in you.

248
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:25,234
You screwed me over.
Just like Magnus!

249
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:29,321
Maybe you two were working together.

250
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:32,199
Maybe you tipped off the police,
and that's why I got caught.

251
00:16:32,282 --> 00:16:34,118
I don't know what you're talking about!

252
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,828
- Tell me the truth!
- I didn't!

253
00:16:35,911 --> 00:16:36,996
- [HOMER] Tell me!
- Magnus!

254
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:38,414
- I didn't!
- Wendy!

255
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,082
- Stop lying!
- I'm not!

256
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,375
- Wendy--
- You bastard!

257
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,919
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

258
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:45,921
- Hit him!
- [WENDY] Stop it!

259
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:47,840
- Harder.
- I said stop!

260
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:49,591
- Come on!
- That's enough!

261
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,177
[HOMER] Well?!

262
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,929
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

263
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:56,682
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:16:57,307 --> 00:16:59,351
You can't kill him yet.

265
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:03,105
We still need him.

266
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,441
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

267
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:11,488
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:16,910
- Here.
- [JOY GRUNTS]

269
00:17:18,078 --> 00:17:19,371
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

270
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:20,914
Okay. Wait.

271
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:26,336
Okay.

272
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:29,381
We're safe now.

273
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,301
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

274
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,388
[DOORKNOB CLICKS]

275
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:39,683
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,726
Shh.

277
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:46,857
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,905
[BOTH GRUNT]

279
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:55,115
- Luna?
- Liam?

280
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:57,201
[LIAM SIGHS IN RELIEF]

281
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:59,411
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:01,789
Oh, sorry. How are you?

283
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:04,124
I'm okay. I was shot but…

284
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,334
But what?

285
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:07,294
Doc helped me.

286
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,379
[LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]

287
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,380
Ms. Happy!

288
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,007
- [IVAN] You okay?
- [LUNA] Yeah.

289
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:13,217
Joy!

290
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,594
Doc, you're alive!

291
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:17,471
You escaped.

292
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:19,181
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

293
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:20,682
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [HAPPY] You're safe.

294
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:23,268
- Doc…
- Doc, thank you so much.

295
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:24,770
- Thank you.
- You saved us.

296
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:26,230
You saved my life.

297
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:29,316
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]

298
00:18:29,399 --> 00:18:32,069
By the way, they are our coworkers
from La Playa Roja.

299
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:34,905
Joy and Ma'am Happy.

300
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:37,533
Well, I'm not happy right now.

301
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,785
Sir, what are we going to do?

302
00:18:40,869 --> 00:18:42,746
- Boss Emil!
- [MAGNUS GROANS]

303
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,164
We've got a problem.

304
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,125
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

305
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:50,337
I have to go back to Mama and Papa.

306
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:52,673
Emil might hurt them
because Olsen and I fought back.

307
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:56,677
Just stay here.

308
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,303
You're safe here. Okay?

309
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:00,264
Liam.

310
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:03,684
Is there anything we can do to help you?

311
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,104
[EMIL OVER PA SYSTEM] <i>Liam Roja.</i>

312
00:19:07,187 --> 00:19:08,522
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:11,692
<i>If you aren't back here in five minutes,</i>

314
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:15,028
you know what'll happen to your mom.

315
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:21,952
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

316
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,090
[DADO] <i>They tried to play us.</i>

317
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:36,133
<i>He's your son?</i>

318
00:19:36,216 --> 00:19:38,051
<i>Is he really dead, or is he still alive?</i>

319
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:41,263
<i>We're making a dish using</i>
<i>whatever ingredients are here.</i>

320
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:43,724
<i>I need you to get</i>
<i>the most important ingredient.</i>

321
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:46,185
- [DADO]<i> Think you're tough, huh?!</i>
- [GRETA] <i>Enough!</i>

322
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:48,520
[EMIL] <i>I'll ask you one last time.</i>

323
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:49,897
<i>Where are the others?</i>

324
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,607
<i>They're hiding in the commissary.</i>

325
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:52,816
[IVAN] <i>I hope this works.</i>

326
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:56,987
<i>Pull a fast one on me again</i>
<i>and I'll shoot you myself.</i>

327
00:19:59,948 --> 00:20:01,116
<i>Go!</i>

328
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:05,829
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
